### Method Overriding

Method overriding allows a subclass to provide a specific implementation of a method defined in its parent class.

```dart
class Animal {
  void makeSound() {
    print('Animal makes a sound');
  }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
  @override
  void makeSound() {
    print('Dog barks');
  }
}

void main() {
  var animal = Animal();
  var dog = Dog();

  animal.makeSound(); // Animal makes a sound
  dog.makeSound();    // Dog barks
}
```

### The @Override Annotation

Use the `@override` annotation to indicate you are intentionally overriding a method. This is optional but recommended.

```dart
class Shape {
  double area() => 0;
  String describe() => 'Shape';
}

class Circle extends Shape {
  double radius;

  Circle(this.radius);

  @override
  double area() => 3.14159 * radius * radius;

  @override
  String describe() => 'Circle with radius $radius';
}
```

### Overriding Operators

Dart allows overriding operators like `+`, `-`, `==`, etc.

```dart
class Vector {
  final int x, y;

  Vector(this.x, this.y);

  @override
  Vector operator +(Vector other) => Vector(x + other.x, y + other.y);

  @override
  bool operator ==(Object other) =>
      other is Vector && x == other.x && y == other.y;

  @override
  int get hashCode => Object.hash(x, y);

  @override
  String toString() => 'Vector($x, $y)';
}

void main() {
  var v1 = Vector(2, 3);
  var v2 = Vector(4, 5);

  print(v1 + v2); // Vector(6, 8)
  print(v1 == Vector(2, 3)); // true
}
```

### Overridable Operators

| Operator | Method |
|----------|--------|
| `+` | `operator +` |
| `-` | `operator -` |
| `*` | `operator *` |
| `/` | `operator /` |
| `~/` | `operator ~/` |
| `%` | `operator %` |
| `[]` | `operator []` |
| `[]=` | `operator []=` |
| `==` | `operator ==` |
| `<` | `operator <` |
| `>` | `operator >` |

> **Key Point:** Always use `@override` when overriding methods. When overriding `==`, you must also override `hashCode` to maintain consistency.

codeExample:
class Point {
  final int x, y;

  Point(this.x, this.y);

  @override
  Point operator +(Point other) => Point(x + other.x, y + other.y);

  @override
  bool operator ==(Object other) =>
      other is Point && x == other.x && y == other.y;

  @override
  int get hashCode => Object.hash(x, y);

  @override
  String toString() => '($x, $y)';
}

void main() {
  var p1 = Point(1, 2);
  var p2 = Point(3, 4);
  var p3 = Point(1, 2);

  print(p1 + p2);  // (4, 6)
  print(p1 == p3); // true
  print(p1);       // (1, 2)
}
